data.title: Did You Catch That? The Mei Blizzard that ALMOST iced the Shock!
Did You Catch That? Watch your back when Moth's playing Lúcio!
data.description: Making huge impact plays in Overwatch don't always require a bunch of ultimate abilities. Sometimes, all you need is a single hero that can break the core of the enemy comp! In this episode of, "Did You Catch That?", we break down a 2019 Playoffs teamfight when San Francisco Shock's Moth flanked the Atlanta Reign's Bastion defense to break them with a single well-timed Soundwave blast.

data.title: Did You Catch That? The Mei Blizzard that ALMOST iced the Shock!
data.description: The 2019 Overwatch League Grand Finals featured some of the most harrowing clutch plays in the game's history. One of these moments featured San Francisco Shock's Rascal scoring a quintuple kill against the Vancouver Titans on the tail end of a teamfight that look doomed for the Shock. In this episode of, "Did You Catch That?", we break down how Rascal may not have been able to pull off this miracle play if the Titans had used their Mei ultimate just a little bit differently.

data.title: Tactics: Bastion ROCKET JUMPS onto a chandelier!
data.description: During the 2019 Grand Finals, the San Francisco Shock's Architect blew the crowd's minds as Bastion when he used his own rockets to blast himself up to a chandelier to win a teamfight vs. the Vancouver Titans. In this episode of Tactics, we examine why and how Architect pulled this move off and how it created an advantage for his team in the ensuing fight.

data.title: Tactics: 1-HP Supercharger? NO PROBLEM!
data.description: Orisa's Supercharger ultimate can provide a team with an immense damage boost during an important teamfight. The tricky part of using it is creating a safe spot to deploy it so the enemy can't destroy it! In this episode of Tactics, we break down how the Atlanta Reign set up a Supercharged teamfight against the San Francisco Shock and highlight how the fight might have ended much differently if the San Francisco Shock had landed just one extra hit of damage!

data.title: Vancouver’s Favorite 2019 Season Moments
data.description: The dominant Vancouver Titans stroll down memory lane through the 2019 season and remember the best (and worst) plays of the year.

data.title: Super’s Super Tour of Philly
data.description: When the Overwatch League Grand Finals comes to your hometown, you’ve got to show them how the locals live. The San Francisco Shock explore the streets of South Philly as Matthew “Super” DeLisi shows his team what it likes to live and play in the “City of Brotherly Love.”

data.title: Did You Catch That? The LUCKIEST Widowmaker Teleporter Shot
data.description: During Stage 4 of the 2019 Overwatch League, the London Spitfire pulled off a crazy play with Symmetra and Widowmaker on Blizzard World by using a Teleporter to secure a surprise first headshot against the Guangzhou Charge. But did you catch just HOW Profit got the shot past Guangzhou Charge’s shields? "Did You Catch That?" is an educational series that highlights exceptional moments in the Overwatch League that might have happened too quickly to catch! It’s all part of Insights: powered by Intel. data.title: San Francisco’s Favorite 2019 Season Moments
data.description: Grinding hard to make it through the 2019 season and secure their place in the Grand Finals, the Shock stars relive their best moments of the season.

data.title: Eye of the Titans: Vancouver’s Run to the Top
data.description: The Vancouver Titans road to the Grand Finals in Philadelphia has been less than “rocky”. Will the Titans topple the Shock and finally TKO the competition?

data.title: Brenjamin Franklin’s Tour of Old Philadelphia
data.description: Benjamin…err…“Brenjamin” Franklin shows a few of the OWL ambassadors and Sideshow around the historical district of Philadelphia and gives them the full (completely false) history of the birth of the nation.

data.title: Tactics: Executing High-Damage Sigma Combos
data.description: Sigma was introduced to the Overwatch League during the 2019 Playoffs and he had a huge impact on the meta! His abilities, Accretion and Gravitic Flux, offer strong crowd-control capabilities that can be used to set up high-damage combos. In this episode of Tactics, we break down three different big combos that Sigma can execute with some help from his teammates. It’s all part of Insights: powered by Intel. Want more Insights? Visit https://overwatchleague.com/en-us/intel-insights.

data.title: Did You Catch That? You Can't Escape THIS Doomfist Combo!
data.description: Doomfist's ultimate, Meteor Strike, deals a ton of damage, but landing one on multiple targets can be a tricky endeavor. In this episode of "Did You Catch That?", we break down an incredibly well-timed Meteor Strike combo from the San Francisco Shock, when the Shock used their Orisa's Halt! ability to lock down three members of the Hangzhou Spark for a massive triple kill. It’s all part of Insights: powered by Intel. Want more Insights? Visit https://overwatchleague.com/en-us/intel-insights.

data.description: Come take a seat around the fire as Mitch "Uber" Leslie regales us with the tale of the San Francisco Shock's epic path to the playoffs in this edition of MasterPath Theatre.

data.title: Vancouver: New Meta, No Problem
data.description: With Sigma propelling his way into the 2019 Overwatch League playoffs, Vancouver has seen some significant changes in their play except for big one: winning. Twilight and Tizi discuss the reforms to the Titans lineup and how they aren’t phased when it comes to change.

data.title: Sigma: The Equation to the Grand Finals

data.title: Best of the 2019 Overwatch League
data.description: Relive the best moments from an amazing 2019 Overwatch League season. From thrilling victories, devastating defeats, crazy comebacks, and moments that make your jaw drop, the 2019 season has been quite the ride.

data.title: Re-Fusion: Philadelphia Swings for the Grand Finals
data.description: Watching London hold the trophy above their heads at the Inaugural season’s Grand Finals was tough for the Philadelphia Fusion. Poko, Carpe and EQO want to let the league know they won’t let history repeat itself and they intend to make it to the Grand Finals for their hometown crowd.

data.title: Meta Report: Stage 4
data.description: The 2-2-2 role lock had a huge impact on the Overwatch League Stage 4 meta! Join Soe, Malik, Bren, Wolf, and Achilios as they walk us through the biggest changes we've seen in this new meta and the teams and players who have found new life! It's all part of Insights: powered by Intel. Want more Insights? Visit https://overwatchleague.com/en-us/intel-insights.

data.title: London Spitfire: Repeat Quest?
data.description: History was captured last year when the London Spitfire took home the Inaugural Season Overwatch League trophy. Can they re-capture history? They’ll have to fight out of the play-in bracket first.

data.title: Watchpoint presents MasterPath Theatre: The Vancouver Titans
data.description: Join us as your bard Seth “Achilios” King recounts the tale of the mighty Vancouver Titans and how they were able to utterly dominate the regular season and brute their way to the 2019 season Overwatch League season playoffs.

data.title: Watchpoint presents MasterPath Theatre: The New York Excelsior
data.description: Join us for another installment of MasterPath Theatre as Erik “Doa” Lonnquist tells the tale of the mighty New York Excelsior and their quest for championship glory in the 2019 Overwatch League season.

data.title: Watchpoint presents MasterPath Theatre: The Atlanta Reign
data.description: It’s a fireside chat with our pal Semmler, who chronicles the Atlanta Reigns rise from the ashes to the Overwatch League Playoffs. As they say… Let’s go, dude.

data.title: Tactics: How Surefour's Hanzo Shut Down the Los Angeles Valiant
data.description: The Los Angeles Valiant were battling the Los Angeles Gladiators on Volskaya Industries. The LA Valiant had to capture 80% of Point B with less than a minute remaining and they had a decent shot at doing it. However, Surefour dismantled the last two pushes of the Los Angeles Valiant. In this episode of Tactics, we break down just how Surefour managed to find those key headshots and how the Los Angeles Valiant failed to mitigate that risk for themselves! It’s all part of Insights: powered by Intel. Want more Insights? Visit https://overwatchleague.com/en-us/intel-insights.
